description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you committed to outstanding patient care? Have you completed your Nursing Associate foundation course or are in the process of completing it in the next 5 – 6 months? If so we would love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be working at Leigh House, which is an acute adolescent psychiatric service, providing inpatient treatment for up to 21 young people between the ages of 12 and 18. Set in its own grounds, an award winning purpose built hospital which provides a comprehensive treatment programme for young people experiencing acute mental illness, such as depression and psychotic disorders.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our nursing associate role is a new role for Leigh House and will bridge the gap between our registered nurses and healthcare support workers enabling us to deliver high quality timely care for patients as part of the Nursing Team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We firmly believe that developing our staff is key to success; we offer exceptional training and development, which providing excellent opportunities to enhance your knowledge and competencies, ensuring you reach your full potential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After joining us we offer a preceptorship programme specifically designed to enable you to consolidate your skills and identify any development needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We welcome informal chats and visits by appointment, please contact Charlotte Miller on 02382310100 to arrange this.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please ensure you read the job description carefully and check the Essential Qualification before applying&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
